 questions they didn't have answers to. Why do you want to stop nuclear power? Because its dangerous is the usual reply. Ask them to elaborate and they get all flustered. Tell them something heretical like 'nuclear power is extremely safe and nobody in the West has ever been killed' and they start clutching at straws. Ask them if they had to choose between nuclear and coal which would it be and they can't give you an answer. Neither, they say. It has to be one or the other you reply. Then they say that 'somebody' should develop a new technology. You ask them why they dont do it themselves and they say they are not rocket scientists. Thats when I reply that some of my friends are in fact rocket scientists and yet none of them foresee anything but either nuclear or coal providing worldwide energy for the foreseeable future.<br>
<br>
If we can get commercial nuclear power accepted then I think its only a small step further to open peoples minds to the possibility of space rockets. We are already on the way. Opinion polls are increasingly showing favourable attitudes to nuclear reactors. It's a pity both space and nuclear technology is largely ignored by the general population. Perhaps together these sciences will be interesting enough to recapture the interest of the masses. <br>
Politicians promise the public what they want to gain support. They tell them what they want to hear. Sometimes not meaning a word of it. We are in the fortunate position of being able to promise a jaded public very great things indeed. Changes that will positively influence their lives forever. Without having to lie. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A> at: 11/12/02 8:20:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mauk2>Mauk2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/12/02 11:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=502.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dr. von Braun's sketch of the space station</span><hr size=1> PREACH IT, PROJECTORION!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
