This kind of attitude among those who fear nuclear power is  common.  I've also asked a number of people to elaborate why nuclear power is so dangerous and they only throw out vague generalities or outright incorrect assumptions.  A lot of them just disagree on the grounds that if it was safe we'd have more nuclear powerplants and no one would complain!  They don't understand that a small, very vocal band of rabid activists have been responsible for the downfall of nuclear power using little else then fear mongering.  Three Mile Island is another reason they use.  That new report that came out recently about there being no abnormal cancer rates can certainly help to fight that assumption now.  Education is definately key but unfortunately the media still loves scare stories so they'll definately default to those people who serve up stories about how installing reactors will lead to nuclear apocalpyse. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 11/13/02 2:42:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1458<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/13/02 4:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=502.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dr. von Braun's sketch of the space station</span><hr size=1> Here's a scare story for the media.<br>
